    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-ceiling lineup led by **Kyle Tucker**, who commands our highest score of 85.90. **Tucker** benefits from an elite combination of a favorable hitter\u2019s park and a exploitable matchup against Ryan Feltner (4.63 xERA), driving his upside significantly above his baseline. **Gunnar Henderson** remains a top-tier play at 81.76, buoyed by a prime leadoff spot and a strong platoon advantage against Gavin Williams, though he carries a 31% rain risk that warrants monitoring. We are also capitalizing on high-efficiency matchups for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Josh Lowe** (71.68); **Lowe** in particular is a priority start because his matchup against the slow-delivering Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez provides a substantial boost for his stolen base potential, an area where we continue to overweight speed to maintain our category edge.\n\nStrategic benching was critical today, as **Nasim Nunez** was the most difficult exclusion from the starting nine. With a score of 57.94, **Nunez** flirted with the marginal threshold, but was ultimately displaced by the superior raw efficiency of our starting outfield and infield cohort. While **Nunez** possesses the sprint speed we crave, the optimizer favored the platoon advantages of **Andy Pages**\u2014who also faces the favorable Feltner matchup\u2014and the higher order-slot reliability of **Luis Robert Jr.** Elsewhere, we are exercising caution with **Jackson Merrill** (55.67) and **Drake Baldwin** (48.10); both face potential platoon disadvantages or tough opposing arms that drag their scores toward the bottom of our active range. We will keep **Marcell Ozuna** and **Coby Mayo** on standby, but given the current projection spread, we are prioritizing players like **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Miguel Vargas** to maximize our daily Roto output.",
